Files:
- e2e/stress-cross-system.e2e.ts (modify config-change-during-dispatch test)

Context:
The test removes the plugin from config while 3 slow calls are in-flight. At least one call MUST fail — otherwise the plugin removal didn't take effect, which means the config change was silently ignored.

Current weak code at lines 209-211:
```typescript
for (const result of slowResults) {
  expect(['fulfilled', 'rejected']).toContain(result.status);
}
```

Replace with:
```typescript
let failCount = 0;
for (const [i, result] of slowResults.entries()) {
  if (result.status === 'rejected') {
    failCount++;
  } else if (result.value.isError) {
    failCount++;
    // Error must identify the cause
    expect(
      /not found|unavailable|removed|disconnected|no matching tab|plugin/i.test(result.value.content),
      `call ${i}: error should identify plugin removal, got: ${result.value.content.slice(0, 100)}`,
    ).toBe(true);
  }
}
// At least one call MUST have failed — proving the plugin removal took effect
expect(failCount).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(1);
```

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the recovery section (plugin restore + fresh echo)
- The key insight: if zero calls fail, the config removal didn't work, which is a system bug

